modules.description: Provides functions to generate pseudo-random numbers using a lagged-Fibonacci algorithm, with entropy sourced from CPU features via mirage-entropy. Works with integers, floats, and byte sequences to produce random values. Used in cryptographic contexts requiring secure random generation within MirageOS environments.

Generates random byte buffers of specified lengths using a provided random generator. Operates on the `g` type and `Cstruct.t` for efficient buffer handling. Initializes the random generator asynchronously before use.
